b/Granite_shield_detail.png/150px-Granite_shield_detail.png?15d44\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"150\" height=\"172\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/Granite_shield_detail.png/225px-Granite_shield_detail.png?15d44 1.5x, /images/thumb/Granite_shield_detail.png/300px-Granite_shield_detail.png?15d44 2x\" data-file-width=\"1269\" data-file-height=\"1453\" /></a></div>\n<p>The <b>Granite shield</b> is a shield made of <a href=\"/w/Granite_equipment\" title=\"Granite equipment\">granite</a>. It requires 50 <a href=\"/w/Defence\" title=\"Defence\">Defence</a> and 50 <a href=\"/w/Strength\" title=\"Strength\">Strength</a> to equip. It has defensive stats equal to the <a href=\"/w/Toktz-ket-xil\" title=\"Toktz-ket-xil\">Toktz-ket-xil</a>, minus the +5 <a href=\"/w/Strength_bonus\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Strength bonus\">strength bonus</a>, and isn't commonly used for <a href=\"/w/Melee\" title=\"Melee\">melee</a> combat as a result.\n</p><p>It is more commonly used than the <a href=\"/w/Rune_kiteshield\" title=\"Rune kiteshield\">Rune kiteshield</a> due to its superior <a href=\"/w/Ranged\" title=\"Ranged\">ranged</a> defence bonus. However, some players choose not to use it due to its weight and slightly lower melee defence bonuses.\n</p>\n<table class=\"rsw-infobox infobox infobox-bonuses infobox\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"10\" class=\"infobox-subheader\"><a href=\"/w/Equipment_Stats#Attack_bonuses\" title=\"Equipment Stats#Attack bonuses\"><img alt=\"Attack icon.png\" src=\"/images/Attack_icon.png?b4bce\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" data-file-width=\"25\" data-file-height=\"25\" /></a>&#160;<a href=\"/w/Equipment_Stats#Attack_bonuses\" title=\"Equipment Stats\">Attack bonuses</a></th><td rowspan=\"15\" class=\"infobox-bonuses-image\" style=\"width:164px\"><a href=\"/w/File:Granite_shield_equipped_male.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Granite shield equipped male.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/Granite_shield_equipped_male.png/164px-Granite_shield_equipped_male.png