ly used for [[melee]] combat as a result.\n\nIt is more commonly used than the [[Rune kiteshield]] due to its superior [[ranged]] defence bonus. However, some players choose not to use it due to its weight and slightly lower melee defence bonuses.\n\n{{Infobox Bonuses\n|astab = 0\n|aslash = 0\n|acrush = 0\n|amagic = -12\n|arange = -8\n|dstab = +40\n|dslash = +42\n|dcrush = +38\n|dmagic = 0\n|drange = +65\n|str = 0\n|rstr = 0\n|mdmg = 0\n|prayer = 0\n|slot = shield\n|image = [[File:Granite shield equipped male.png|170px]]\n|altimage = [[File:Granite shield equipped female.png|170px]]\n}}\n\n==Treasure Trails==\n{{EmoteClueHeader}}\n{{EmoteClue|tier=elite|emote=Jump for Joy|location=Entrance of the [[Ancient Cavern]]|item1=Granite shield|item2=splitbark body|item3=Rune heraldic helm|img3=Rune helm (h1)|cost3={{min|{{GEP|Rune helm (h1)}}|{{GEP|Rune helm (h2)}}|{{GEP|Rune helm (h3)}}|{{GEP|Rune helm (h4)}}|{{GEP|Rune helm (h5)}}}}}}\n{{EmoteClueBottom}}\n\n==Item sources==\n{{Drop sources|Granite shield}}\n\n==Trivia==\n*Although the shield has lower melee defence bonuses than a [[Rune kiteshield]], it has a higher Defence requirement. The granite shield is one of two pieces of the set with weaker melee defence stats (the other being [[Granite legs]]) than its rune equivalent.\n*The granite shield may have been modelled after the real life island {{wp|Gran Canaria}}, due to its striking similarity in shape.\n\n{{Granite items}}\n[[Category:Melee armour]]"}